# clsx Best Practices

## Context

- Provides guidelines for using clsx in component styling
- Ensures clean and readable conditional class logic
- Helps maintain consistent styling patterns

## Critical Rules

- Use clsx for conditional class name management to simplify JSX
- Keep class name logic straightforward to enhance readability
- Combine clsx with Tailwind CSS for efficient styling
- Avoid nesting too many conditions to maintain clarity
- Use descriptive class names to improve maintainability
- Group related classes together for better organization
- Use early returns for complex conditional logic
- Document complex class combinations when necessary

## Examples

